  <prompt>
    Build and deploy the `LegalWorkspace` solution to the dev environment via the `dataverse-deploy` skill. This deploy ships the Wave 3 migrations:
    - `FilePreviewDialog.tsx` now consumes canonical `<SendEmailDialog />` (task 051)
    - Any additional consumers migrated by task 053
    - Implicit dependency on `@spaarke/ui-components` shipping the canonical wrapper (already published by Wave 1)

    Pre-deploy checks: confirm `@spaarke/ui-components` is at a version that includes the canonical wrapper (Wave 1 + task 050/052 outputs). Confirm `npm run build` is clean in LegalWorkspace. Confirm no straggling lint errors.

    Post-deploy verification: open the deployed LegalWorkspace in the dev environment, navigate to a file preview surface, confirm no console errors on page load (deferred E2E click-test is task 055).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Deployment engineer familiar with the `dataverse-deploy` skill conventions for LegalWorkspace solution builds. Knows the build pipeline (Vite + `npm install --legacy-peer-deps --no-audit --no-fund` per CLAUDE.md §11), the solution-import path, and the dev environment target.
  </role>

  <goal>
    LegalWorkspace solution deployed to dev with Wave 3 Bug-fix changes shipped. `npm run build` clean. `npm run lint` clean. Solution imported successfully (no Dataverse import errors). Smoke loading the LegalWorkspace surface in dev shows no JavaScript console errors. Ready for task 055 (functional smoke test).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      LegalWorkspace is the React/Vite solution at `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/`. It bundles `@spaarke/ui-components` and ships as a Dataverse web resource via the existing deploy pipeline.

      Wave 3 changes affecting this deploy:
      - `FilePreviewDialog.tsx` migrated to canonical `<SendEmailDialog />` (task 051)
      - Removed inline `fetch` + legacy `onSend` callback
      - Added `onSent` / `onError` handlers + Fluent toast/banner for results

      Per CLAUDE.md §11, LegalWorkspace's `package-lock.json` may be stale — use `npm install --legacy-peer-deps --no-audit --no-fund` not `npm ci`. The build script in the solution handles this automatically.

      Per `dataverse-deploy` skill: the deploy is solution-scoped. Multiple solutions can be co-resident in dev. The deploy does NOT touch BFF or schema — those are separate pipelines.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/ (build root)</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/package.json</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/vite.config.ts (or equivalent build config)</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/FilePreview/FilePreviewDialog.tsx (migrated by task 051)</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/dataverse-deploy/SKILL.md (deploy procedure reference)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §11">Use `npm install --legacy-peer-deps --no-audit --no-fund` for LegalWorkspace; do NOT use `npm ci`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Deploy targets DEV environment only — do NOT deploy to prod from this task.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-033">No code changes during deploy — this task is mechanical packaging only. Any code-level issue surfaced by the build escalates back to task 051 / 053 / 050.</constraint>
    <constraint source="repo">Solution import MUST succeed without errors. Warnings acceptable if pre-existing.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Document the deploy result (timestamp + dev environment URL) in `notes/wave-3-deploy.md`.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/spec.md</file>
