  <steps>
    <step order="1">Pre-deploy check: verify `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/` builds clean. Run from the solution root:
      <code>
      npm install --legacy-peer-deps --no-audit --no-fund
      npm run build
      npm run lint
      </code>
      If any step fails, escalate to tasks 051 / 053 / 050 — do NOT attempt deploy with broken build.
    </step>
    <step order="2">Confirm `@spaarke/ui-components` resolves to a version containing the canonical wrapper. Inspect `node_modules/@spaarke/ui-components/dist/index.d.ts` (or equivalent) for `SendEmailDialog` export and the canonical `ISendEmailDialogProps` shape (no `onSend`).</step>
    <step order="3">Invoke `dataverse-deploy` skill with target = dev environment + solution = LegalWorkspace. Follow the skill's deploy procedure for solution-scoped deploys.</step>
    <step order="4">Monitor deploy output. On success: capture the deploy timestamp + dev environment URL. On failure: capture the error message, escalate based on category:
      - Build error → escalate to task 051
      - Solution-import conflict → escalate to project owner
      - Auth failure → re-authenticate per `dataverse-deploy` skill troubleshooting
    </step>
    <step order="5">Post-deploy: navigate to LegalWorkspace in dev (browser). Open the JS console. Load a page that surfaces FilePreviewDialog (open a file). Confirm zero console errors during load. NOTE: clicking "Send by Email" is task 055 — do NOT execute the send from this task.</step>
    <step order="6">Write deploy summary to `notes/wave-3-deploy.md`: timestamp, dev environment URL, console-error check result, any warnings observed.</step>
    <step order="7">Update `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 054 ✅ completed.</step>
    <step order="8">Update `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/current-task.md` per task-execute protocol: status → completed, advance to next pending task (055).</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="bash">Run build + lint locally</tool>
    <tool name="dataverse-deploy">Solution deploy to dev</tool>
    <tool name="write">Create `notes/wave-3-deploy.md` deploy summary</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="notes">projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/wave-3-deploy.md (NEW — deploy summary)</output>
    <output type="deploy">LegalWorkspace solution deployed to dev environment</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/` `npm run build` exits 0.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/` `npm run lint` exits 0.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`dataverse-deploy` skill reports successful solution import to dev environment.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">LegalWorkspace surface loads in dev with zero JS console errors on page load.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`notes/wave-3-deploy.md` exists with timestamp + dev URL + console-check result.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`TASK-INDEX.md` marks task 054 ✅ completed.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Deploy escalation policy: if any deploy step fails, fix the upstream code task FIRST, then re-run this task — do NOT patch around it. The Wave 3 code is settled by tasks 050–053; if the deploy fails, that signals an upstream defect that needs fixing in its source task.

    Console-error scan in step 5 is a pre-flight check for task 055 (functional smoke). A clean page load does NOT prove the send-email flow works — it only proves the migrated code does not crash on render. Functional verification is task 055.

    `dataverse-deploy` skill conventions: per `.claude/skills/dataverse-deploy/SKILL.md`. If the skill is unavailable or has changed since project pipeline ran, fall back to the manual deploy procedure in `docs/guides/PCF-DEPLOYMENT-GUIDE.md` (the solution-import steps are analogous).
  </notes>

